{{Documentation subpage}} <!-- Categories go at the bottom of this page and interwikis go in Wikidata. --> This is a documentation assistance template. It creates a link to a personal JS page with the default display of "your JS".
== Parameters == * '''js''': set the JS page: ** skin: current skin ** cologne: Cologne Blue ** modern: Modern ** monobook: MonoBook ** vector: Vector ** common: common (default) * '''disp''': set the displayed text; defaults to "your JS"
== Examples == {{markup |<nowiki>{{yourjs}}</nowiki> |{{yourjs}}
|<nowiki>{{yourjs|js=monobook}}</nowiki> |{{yourjs|js=monobook}}
|<nowiki>{{yourjs|js=monobook|disp=Monobook JS}}</nowiki> |{{yourjs|js=monobook|disp=Monobook JS}}
}}
== See also == * {{tl|yourcss}}
<includeonly>{{Sandbox other|| <!-- Categories go here, and interwikis go in Wikidata --> [[Category:Documentation assistance templates]] }}</includeonly>

